      "text/plain": [
       "[{'type': 'text',\n",
       "  'text': 'The full form of **RAG** depends on the context, but it most commonly refers to:\\n\\n### 1. In Artificial Intelligence (AI):\\n**Retrieval-Augmented Generation**\\nThis is a technique used to give Large Language Models (like ChatGPT) access to specific, external data that wasn\\'t in their original training set. It helps the AI provide more accurate, up-to-date, and fact-based answers.\\n\\n### 2. In Project Management and Business:\\n**Red, Amber, Green**\\nThis is often called a \"RAG status\" or \"Traffic Light\" system. It is used to indicate the health of a project:\\n*   **Red:** There are critical issues (needs immediate attention).\\n*   **Amber:** There are some risks or delays (needs monitoring).\\n*   **Green:** Everything is on track.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Other less common meanings:**\\n*   **Remote Area Group:** Often used in geography or logistics.\\n*   **Resource Allocation Group:** Used in corporate management.\\n*   **Ring-Aged Gland:** A term used in biology/endocrinology.',\n",
       "  'extras': {'signature': ''}}]"
      ]
     },
